Asked @Apple #Siri to ‚Äúturn off the air conditioner.‚Äù Only one of three was on, but it still asked, ‚ÄúWhich one?‚Äù and listed all three. We often expect too much from #AI. This behaviour doesn‚Äôt need complex GPTs ‚Äî not even AI. A PM and engineers could‚Äôve just coded the implicit actions. What gets in the way is more around prioritisation, management, GTM, investment, messaging cohesion, release thematics and people dynamics than engineering. Now that‚Äôs where AI could truly make a difference by reducing the alignment overhead and the ancillary cost perception.

Engineering is already getting easier (with what I see from our work at #Postman) we need to make large scale #collaboration easier.

Being able to build software is actually so so cool üöÄ

On my Japan trip my friend suggested I build a Yen conversion app, so we‚Äôll stop manually calculating prices. I made a quick PWA in an hour while everyone was sleeping the next day.

I could have totally downloaded an already existing app, but I like building things and I was able to make it:

‚úÖ 100% advertisement free
‚úÖ Offline support
‚úÖ UX streamlined for what we needed

I watched my friends use the app throughout the day. I noted times they struggled and was able to change the UX the next day.

The app automatically updated because it was a PWA ü§© -- super cool feeling to do user testing and surprise people by fixing issues almost right away üòÇ

It felt very cool to actually use what would normally be a pet project : - )

I'm still jet lagged so I've been polishing a v2 of the app the past few nights:

‚úÖ Created a logo
‚úÖ Added mostly all currencies in addition to USD
‚úÖ Setup a cron job to cache historic prices for the yen conversion chart (Shoutout to @ValDotTown  for the really good DX + docs for creating cron jobs/serverless functions)
